<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-52-0219 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper describes the legal aspects of the lands unsuitable for miningpetition process. It relates facts on the land ownership and the denialof their rights to access coal on their property. It also makes claimson the intent of the law (Public Law 95-87) when it said mining couldbe declared unsuitable for an area where mining and reclamation werenot technologically or economically feasible. Selected portions of thelaws is reviewed section by section.</TEXT></DOC>